channel.name: CSPAN 3 US
channel.title: Lectures in History
channel.desc: American University professor Laura Beers teaches a class on Winston Churchill and the special relationship between Great Britain and the U.S during World War II and the Cold War.

channel.name: CSPAN 3 US
channel.title: Reel America
channel.desc: This portion of a National Churchill Museum film tells the story of the March 5, 1946 Sinews of Peace speech by the former British Prime Minister at Westminster College in Fulton, Missouri, best known for Churchill's reference to the Iron Curtain.

channel.name: CSPAN 3 US
channel.title: The Presidency
channel.desc: John Adams as a political theorist is the subject of a discussion about his influence on the U.S. Constitution, especially on the democratic foundations of separation of powers, checks and balances.

channel.name: CSPAN 3 US
channel.title: Pope Francis 2015 Address to a Joint Session of Congress
channel.desc: Pope Francis addresses a joint meeting of Congress in 2015, the first pontiff in history to address both chambers.

channel.name: CSPAN 3 US
channel.title: Fall of Saigon Annoucement
channel.desc: Secretary of State Henry Kissinger announces the end of the Vietnam War on April 29, 1975; he describes the loss and evacuation of Saigon.

channel.name: CSPAN 3 US
channel.title: High School Advanced Placement - U.S. History Exam 2025
channel.desc: Jason Stacy and Matthew Ellington, co-authors of "Fabric of a Nation: A History With Skills and Sources," for the AP U.S. history course, talk about the high school advanced placement U.S. history exam.
